# .gitleaksignore
#
# Whitelists known false positives from gitleaks secret scanning.
# Each entry is a SHA256 hash of the offending line, or a file path pattern.
#
# To generate a hash for a false positive:
#   echo -n "the offending line" | sha256sum

# .env.example contains placeholder values only (sk-ant-your-key-here, AIza-your-key-here, etc.)
# These are not real secrets.
.env.example

# Documentation may contain example API key formats for illustration
docs/**

# Build output is not committed but is listed here defensively
build/**
.svelte-kit/**
